The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                 NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	Akola, Feb. 20 (PTI): A man has threatened to immolate himself in front of the collectorate here because the authorities failed to give him an appointment letter for a job that had been confirmed a decade back.          
	Nilkanth Vishwas Deshmukh has threatened this extreme step as his job with the Maharashtra Jeevan Pradhikaran had apparently been confirmed in 1998 but in spite of repeated reminders, he had not been allowed to join. Recently, he was informed he was ineligible owing to age bar.                  
	Panaji (PTI): Former Goa minister and sitting MLA Anatasio Monserratte, facing a charge of attempted murder, was arrested on Wednesday in connection with a mob attack on a Panaji police station in which 15 policemen were injured.                  
	Vellore (PTI): Madras High Court has come down heavily on the shoddy manner of investigations into alleged gang rape of a convicts wife by four jail officials and her subsequent disappearance. Four special police teams were formed on Tuesday to trace her.                  
	Nashik (PTI): An autorickshaw driver who was injured when a security guard opened fire during a street brawl died on Wednesday morning, hospital sources said. Twenty seven persons have been arrested in this connection.                  
	Ahmedabad (PTI): Police fired tear gas shells to quell a stone-pelting crowd in Sangarwa on the outskirts of the city, officials said. Trouble brewed on Tuesday when municipal contractors went to the village to collect rubbles of houses demolished by authorities and were confronted by angry villagers. One police constable was injured in the clash.                  
	 Akola (PTI): Unidentified persons allegedly looted a donation box of a temple in Washim district and fled with Rs 10,000, police said on Wednesday. This is the second incident of temple theft in a week.                                                                                                                           
